Speciation in the Plumularia setacea complex
Project
View
Global Coryne eximia phylogeography: samples welcome!
Project
Coryne eximia is a hydroid with a free medusa occurring worldwide in cool to temperate water, often associated with blue mussels. It can be a fouling species and is potentailly a spreading or invasive species, although an unproblematic one. Using a phylogeographic approach based in 16S sequences, the project aims at finding out if the populations have a recent origin and where this origin might be. Any samples in alcohol are highly welcome! Species info see : http://www.marinespecies.org/hydrozoa/aphia.php?p=taxdetails&id=151860
